devdoc.author: @psychoplasma @pash7ka * Storage consists of a linked list of ids and data, stored in maps, wehre key is a job id. Job id is created from timestamp and a nonce, which is current count of jobs for specific timestamp. After adding a job, nonce for it's timestamp is incremented. When canceling a job, nonce is NOT decremented. * This contract should not be used standalone, it is designed as a part of CronJob

params.nonce: Index of job scheduled to specified timestamp
params.time: When job has to be executed

getJob(uint256).return: (time, callee, data) Time of the job, target contract, message to the contract
